(a_n)
\lim_{N \to \infty} \sum^N_{n = 2} a_n
S_N = \sum_{n = 1}^N = (-1)^{n+1} \frac{1}{n}
t_{3N} = \frac{1}{2} s_{2N}
(a_n)
\lim_{N \to \infty} \sum_{n=2}^N \dfrac{1}{n(n-1)}=\lim_{N\to \infty}\sum_{n=2}^N\dfrac{n-(n-1)}{n(n-1)}
\lim_{N\to \infty}\sum_{n=2}^N\left(\dfrac{n}{n(n-1)}-\dfrac{n-1}{n(n-1)}\right)\overset{(1)}{=}\lim_{N\to\infty}\left(1-\dfrac{1}{N}\right)=1
\left\{\dfrac{1}{n}\right\}_{n=1}^\infty\to0
\displaystyle\sum_{n=2}^N(\dfrac{1}{n-1}-\frac{1}{n})=1-\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{3}+\cdots-\frac{1}{N-1}+\frac{1}{N-1}-\frac{1}{N}
